.TH "VMCTL" "1" "March 2026" "" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
vmctl \- interactive quickemu wrapper for starting and managing local
virtual machines
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]vmctl\f[R] [\f[CR]\-h\f[R]] [\f[CR]\-\-clear\-cache\f[R]]
[\f[CR]\-\-clear\-iso\-cache\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]vmctl\f[R] is a \f[CR]gum\f[R]\-based interactive wrapper around
\f[B]quickemu\f[R] and \f[B]quickget\f[R].
.PP
It scans \f[CR]\[ti]/quickemu\f[R] for \f[CR]*.conf\f[R] files and
presents interactive menus for VM selection and lifecycle operations.
It can also drive \f[B]quickget\f[R] to create a new VM configuration
from the upstream OS catalog.
.PP
When a VM is created, \f[B]vmctl\f[R] caches the downloaded installer
ISO under the user cache directory and replaces the VM\-local copy with
a symlink when possible.
Recreating the same OS, release, and edition reuses the cached ISO and
cached template config instead of downloading the installer again.
.PP
Features include:
.IP \[bu] 2
creating new VMs from the quickget catalog
.IP \[bu] 2
reusing cached installer ISOs for repeated VM creation
.IP \[bu] 2
starting and stopping VMs
.IP \[bu] 2
opening SPICE connections to running VMs
.IP \[bu] 2
listing, creating, applying, and deleting snapshots
.IP \[bu] 2
displaying VM configuration and disk information
.IP \[bu] 2
resizing stopped VM disk images
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[CR]\-h\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-help\f[R]
Show usage help and exit.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-clear\-cache\f[R]
Remove the cached quickget OS list stored under the user cache
directory.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-clear\-iso\-cache\f[R]
Remove cached installer ISOs and cached template configs stored under
the user cache directory.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
\f[B]vmctl\f[R] requires:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]gum\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]quickemu\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]quickget\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]qemu\-img\f[R]
.PP
The SPICE connect action also requires either:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]spicy\f[R] from \f[CR]spice\-client\-gtk\f[R], or
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]remote\-viewer\f[R] from \f[CR]virt\-viewer\f[R]
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[CR]\[ti]/quickemu\f[R]
Default directory scanned for VM configuration files.
.TP
\f[CR]$XDG_CACHE_HOME/vmctl/quickget\-list.csv\f[R]
Cached copy of the quickget catalog when \f[CR]XDG_CACHE_HOME\f[R] is
set.
.TP
\f[CR]\[ti]/.cache/vmctl/quickget\-list.csv\f[R]
Cached copy of the quickget catalog when \f[CR]XDG_CACHE_HOME\f[R] is
not set.
.TP
\f[CR]$XDG_CACHE_HOME/vmctl/isos/\f[R]
Cached installer ISOs and template configs for quickget\-created VMs
when \f[CR]XDG_CACHE_HOME\f[R] is set.
.TP
\f[CR]\[ti]/.cache/vmctl/isos/\f[R]
Cached installer ISOs and template configs for quickget\-created VMs
when \f[CR]XDG_CACHE_HOME\f[R] is not set.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
vmctl
vmctl \-\-clear\-cache
vmctl \-\-clear\-iso\-cache
vmctl \-h
.EE
.SH NOTES
Snapshot apply and delete operations should be performed only while the
VM is stopped.
.PP
Disk resize changes the virtual disk image size.
The guest OS may still require partition and filesystem expansion after
the VM is booted.
